{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"All content for the site lives in "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"src/content"}]},{"type":"text","value":". The starter will generate a\nsite comprising of three main sets of pages."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h1","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Generic Pages"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Generic pages can be found in the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"src/content/pages"}]},{"type":"text","value":". Each consists of a\nmarkdown document and a directory of images."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Home Page"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"About Page"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"404"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"You can view the 404 page when running your site in development by navigating to\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"localhost:8000/404"}]},{"type":"text","value":". Both the Home Page and the About Page must include an\nimage at least 2400px wide."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h1","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Resources"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"There are two kinds of resource pages: Articles and Projects."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Articles"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Articles can be found in "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"src/content/articles"}]},{"type":"text","value":". Like Pages they consist of a\nmarkdown document and a directory for images. They must include a set of\nfrontmatter data used in building the site. Articles are displayed in\nchronological order, starting with the most recent. They should be categorised\nand tagged. The title for the article should be defined in the frontmatter, not\nin the markdown. You can change the name of the resource from\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"src/site-config.js"}]},{"type":"text","value":", and this will update across the site, including links and\nURLs. For example you could change ‘Articles’ to ‘Posts’ or ‘Writings’. All\nArticles must include an image that is at least 2400px wide."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Projects"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Projects are structured the same way as Articles, though they don't supportz"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\ncategorisation. If you don’t want to include projects pages it is easy to remove\nthem from the site. Like Articles you can change the name of the resource from\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"src/site-config.js"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and like Articles, Projects must include an image."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h1","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Tags and Categories"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Tags"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Both Articles and Projects allow you to define keywords in their frontmatter. In\nboth cases they will be used in the page metadata, however in the case of\nArticles the article they will also be used to associate tags with that Article.\nThese tags become links that can be used to view all Articles that have been\ntagged with a given tag. You can add as many tags as you want to an Article or\nProject."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Categories"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Articles also allow you to define a single Category per article. These are much\nhigher-level than tags. Like tags, they will become links which can be used to\nview all Articles that fall within a given category."}]}],"data":{"quirksMode":false}},"wordCount":{"words":349},"timeToRead":2,"frontmatter":{"keywords":"site, website, blog, pages","image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7772020725388602,"src":"/gatsby-starter-skeleton/static/main-e4ca53d1d9f3aed86588abbaa1fd48b8-381d6.jpg","srcSet":"/gatsby-starter-skeleton/static/main-e4ca53d1d9f3aed86588abbaa1fd48b8-62f05.jpg 200w,\n/gatsby-starter-skeleton/static/main-e4ca53d1d9f3aed86588abbaa1fd48b8-dc2b4.jpg 400w,\n/gatsby-starter-skeleton/static/ma